Serena Williams and Caroline Wozniacki will attempt to set up a fascinating women’s final when they take on seemingly overmatched opponents in the US Open last four.

After a tournament of upsets, Williams will come up against No 17 seed Ekaterina Makarova of Russia.

Meanwhile Wozniacki tackles world No 39 Peng Shuai, who had previously made her name more as more of a doubles expert.

