Two perennial nearly-men, Tomas Berdych and Marin Cilic, were facing each other to try to make the men’s semi-finals. 

The other player in the last four will be the winner of the overnight match between Roger Federer and Frenchman Gael Monfils.

Andy Murray crashed out at the quarter-final stage after losing to Novak Djokovic in four sets.

